title: Taliban kill Islamic State leader who masterminded airport bombing that left 13 US service members dead
description: The Tailban have killed an Islamic State group leader who masterminded the Kabul airport suicide bombing that left 13 US service members dead.

title: Uber Eats driver dismembered after 'demonic murder' while 'delivering food to suspect'
description: An Uber Eats driver was dismembered after a "demonic" murder while delivering food, authorities have said.

title: Investigation under way after research rocket fired from Sweden lands in Norway
description: An investigation is under way after a research rocket fired from Sweden malfunctioned and ended up landing in Norway.

title: First private moon landing appears to have failed
description: An attempt to land the first privately-funded spacecraft on the moon appears to have failed.

title: Agonising choice of NHS doctor fleeing Sudan has left her riddled with guilt
description: As the UK government begins evacuating British citizens from Sudan, many have made their own way out to safety.

title: British American Tobacco to pay £512m for North Korea 'misconduct'
description: British American Tobacco (BAT) has agreed a $635.2m (£512m) penalty with US authorities relating to "misconduct" in sanctions-hit North Korea.

title: Singer Harry Belafonte used his platform to help break down racial barriers
description: "Get them to sing your song and they will want to know who you are, and if they've made that first step, we can find a solution to hate."

title: Shares plunge at First Republic Bank as it reveals more than $100bn of withdrawals
description: Shares in First Republic Bank have tumbled to a new record low after the troubled US regional lender admitted last month's banking crisis sparked a customer deposit flight of more than $100bn.

title: Families in Sudan forced to hide during fighting as others flee Khartoum
description: For 22-year-old Sarah, it was like any other normal Saturday at her family home in Khartoum’s al-Riyadh district.

title: Scientists use AI and underwater microphones to detect tsunamis and earthquakes
description: An early warning system for tsunamis and underwater earthquakes - powered by artificial intelligence - has been developed by scientists.

title: Britons face perilous escape from Sudan with chaos and unpredictability on the ground
description: There are two main risks for the UK's mission to evacuate thousands of British passport-holders out of Sudan: the fighting and the logistics.

title: India's population to surpass China by end of the month
description: India is expected to be the world's most populous country by the end of this month, eclipsing an aging China, according to the United Nations.

title: Joe Biden formally announces he will run for a second term as US president
description: Joe Biden has formally announced that he is running for re-election in 2024, asking voters to give him more time to "finish the job".

title: UK begins evacuation mission for Britons trapped in Sudan
description: A mission to evacuate British nationals from Sudan has begun - as around 4,000 UK passport holders remain stranded amid heavy fighting.

title: 70 bodies pulled from sea and 1,200 people rescued after boats capsize trying to reach Europe
description: At least 70 bodies have been pulled from the sea and 1,200 people have been rescued after dozens of packed boats attempted to cross the Mediterranean.

title: 'Every hour counts': Ceasefire underway in Sudan as UK govt faces evacuation pressures
description: A 72-hour ceasefire between Sudan's two warring factions is underway as the UK government faces pressure to "not miss the window" of opportunity for evacuations and delivering urgent aid.
